quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,"Nay! I swear by this city",footnotes:182716:1|182717:2
  90,2,"– this city wherein you have been rendered violable–",footnotes:182718:1
  90,3,"and I swear by the parent and his offspring:",footnotes:182719:1
  90,4,"Verily We have created man into toil and hardship.",footnotes:182720:1
  90,5,"Does he think that no one can overpower him?",footnotes:182721:1
  90,6,"He says: “I have squandered enormous wealth.”",footnotes:182722:1
  90,7,"Does he believe that none has seen him?",footnotes:182723:1
  90,8,"Did We not grant him two eyes,"
  90,9,"and a tongue and two lips?",footnotes:182724:1
  90,10,"And did We not show him the two highroads (of good and evil)?",footnotes:182725:1
  90,11,"But he did not venture to scale the difficult steep.",footnotes:182726:1
  90,12,"And what do you know what that difficult steep is?"
  90,13,"It is freeing someone's neck from slavery;"
  90,14,"or giving food on a day of hunger"
  90,15,"to an orphan near of kin;"
  90,16,"or to a destitute lying in dust;",footnotes:182727:1
  90,17,"and, then besides this, he be one of those who believed, and enjoined upon one another steadfastness and enjoined upon one another compassion.",footnotes:182728:1|182729:2
  90,18,"These are the People of the Right Hand."
  90,19,"As for those who rejected Our Signs, they are the People of the Left Hand.",footnotes:182730:1
  90,20,"Upon them shall be a Fire that will hem them in.",footnotes:182731:1
